HEADWORD: Langaha
<hw>Lan"ga*ha</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
curious colubriform snake of the genus <gen>Xyphorhynchus</gen>, from
Madagascar. It is brownish red, and its nose is prolonged in the form of
a sharp blade.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

